      "Crew evacuated to emergency muster stations",
      "Daily operational updates sent to BSEE"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 27, 2014, while drilling at 15,902 feet in a salt zone, the Maersk Valiant experienced a gas influx resulting in approximately 55 barrels of mud being discharged onto the rig floor. The well was shut-in using the Upper Annular, but the shut-in pressure caused fracturing of the formation and 22 inch casing shoe. A second influx of 16 barrels occurred on November 21, 2014, which was contained with no surface release. No injuries or environmental pollution resulted from either incident.",
